obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (26123)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content `This Act may be called the Bihar Reorganisation Act, 2000.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26123&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (26124)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26124&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day^1"`
  line `means the day which the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint;`
  line
  line `(b) "article" means an article of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(c) "assembly constituency", "council constituency" and "parliamentary constituency" have the`
  line `same meanings as in the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950);`
  line
  line `(d) "Election Commission" means the Election Commission appointed by the President under`
  line `article 324;`
  line
  line `(e) "existing State of Bihar" means the State of Bihar as existing immediately before the`
  line `appointed day;`
  line
  line `(f) "law" includes any enactment, ordinance, regulation, order, bye-law, rule, scheme, notification`
  line `or other instrument having, immediately before the appointed day, the force of law in the whole or in`
  line `any part of the existing State of Bihar;`
  line
  line `(g) "notified order" means an order published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(h) "population ratio", in relation to the States of Bihar and Jharkhand, means the ratio of`
  line `645.30:218.44;`
  line
  line `(i) "sitting member", in relation to either House of Parliament or of the Legislature of the existing`
  line `State of Bihar, means a person who immediately before the appointed day, is a member of that`
  line House;
  line
  line `(j) "successor State", in relation to the existing State of Bihar, means the State of Bihar or`
  line Jharkhand;
  line
  line `(k) "transferred territory" means the territory which on the appointed day is transferred from the`
  line `existing State of Bihar to the State of Jharkhand;`
  line
  line `(l) "treasury" includes a sub-treasury; and`
  line
  line `(m) any reference to a district, tahsil or other territorial division of the existing State of Bihar`
  line `shall be construed as a reference to the area comprised within that territorial division on the appointed`
  line day.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 15th November, 2000, vide notification No. S.O. 829(E), dated 14th September, 2000, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part`
  line `II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (26125)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Formation of Jharkhand State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26125&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, there shall be formed a new`
  line `State to be known as the State of Jharkhand comprising the following territories of the existing State of`
  line `Bihar, namely:—`
  line
  line `Bokaro, Chatra, Deogarh, Dhanbad, Dumka, Garhwa, Giridih, Godda, Gumla, Hazaribagh,`
  line `Kodarma, Lohardaga, Pakur, Palamau, Ranchi, Sahebganj, Singhbhum (East) and Singhbhum (West)`
  line districts,
  line
  line `and thereupon the said territories shall cease to form part of the existing State of Bihar.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (26126)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `State of Bihar and territorial divisions thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26126&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, the State of`
  line `Bihar shall comprise the territories of the existing State of Bihar other than those specified in section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (26127)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Amendment of the First Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26127&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in the`
  line `First Schedule to the Constitution, under the heading "I. THE STATES",—`
  line
  line `(a) in the paragraph relating to the territories of the State of Bihar, the following shall be added at`
  line `the end, namely:—`
  line
  line `"and the territories specified in section 3 of the Bihar Reorganisation Act, 2000";`
  line
  line `(b) after entry 27, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"28. Jharkhand: The territories specified in section 3 of the Bihar Reorganisation Act, 2000.".`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (26128)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Saving powers of State Governments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26128&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in the foregoing provisions of this Part shall be`
  line `deemed to affect the power of the Government of Bihar or Jharkhand to alter, after the appointed day, the`
  line `name, area or boundaries of any district or other territorial division in the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (26129)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Amendment of the Fourth Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26129&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in`
  line `the Fourth Schedule to the Constitution, in the Table,--`
  line
  line `(a) entries 4 to 29 shall be renumbered as entries 5 to 30 respectively;`
  line
  line `(b) in entry 3, for the figures "22" the figures "16" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(c) after entry 3, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"4. Jharkhand...................................... 6".`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (26130)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Allocation of sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26130&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, the twenty-two sitting`
  line `members of the Council of States representing the existing State of Bihar shall be deemed to have been`
  line `elected to fill the seats allotted to the States of Bihar and Jharkhand, as specified in the First Schedule to`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of such sitting members shall remain unaltered.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (26131)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Representation in the House of the People.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26131&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, there shall be`
  line `allocated 40 seats to the successor State of Bihar, and 14 to the successor State of Jharkhand, in the House`
  line `of the People and in the First Schedule to the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950), under`
  line `heading "I. STATES:",---`
  line
  line `(a) for entry 4, the following entry shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"4. Bihar 53 7 5 40 7 .";`
  line
  line `(b) entries 10 to 25 shall be renumbered as entries 11 to 26 respectively;`
  line
  line `(c) after entry 9, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"10. Jharkhand .. .. .. 14 1 5".`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (26132)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26132&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed`
  line `day, the Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies Order, 1976, shall stand amended as`
  line `directed in the Second Schedule to this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (26133)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Provision as to sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26133&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every sitting member of the House of the People`
  line `representing a constituency which, on the appointed day by virtue of the provisions of section 10, stands`
  line `allotted, with or without alteration of boundaries, to the successor State of Bihar or Jharkhand, shall be`
  line `deemed to have been elected to the House of the People by that constituency as so allotted.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of such sitting members shall remain unaltered.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (26134)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Provisions as to Legislative Assemblies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26134&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The number of seats as on the appointed day in`
  line `the Legislative Assemblies of the States of Bihar and Jharkhand shall be two hundred and forty-three and`
  line `eighty-one respectively.`
  line
  line `(2) In the Second Schedule to the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950), under heading`
  line `"I. States",--`
  line
  line `(a) for entry 4, the following entry shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"4. Bihar 318 45 29 243 39 ...";`
  line
  line `(b) entries 11 to 27 shall be renumbered as entries 12 to 28 respectively;`
  line
  line `(c) after entry 10, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"11. Jharkhand .. .. .. 81 9 28".`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (26135)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Allocation of sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26135&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every sitting member of the Legislative Assembly of the`
  line `existing State of Bihar elected to fill a seat in that Assembly from a constituency which on the appointed`
  line `day by virtue of the provisions of section 10 stands allotted, with or without alteration of boundaries, to`
  line `the State of Jharkhand shall, on and from that day, cease to be a member of the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `Bihar and shall be deemed to have been elected to fill a seat in the Legislative Assembly of Jharkhand`
  line `from that constituency as so allotted.`
  line
  line `(2) All other sitting members of the Legislative Assembly of the existing State of Bihar shall continue`
  line `to be members of the Legislative Assembly of that State and any such sitting member representing a`
  line `constituency the extent, or the name and extent of which are altered by virtue of the provisions of section`
  line `10 shall be deemed to have been elected to the Legislative Assembly of Bihar by that constituency as so`
  line altered.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the Legislative`
  line `Assemblies of Bihar and Jharkhand shall be deemed to be duly constituted on the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(4) The sitting member of the Legislative Assembly of the existing State of Bihar nominated to that`
  line `Assembly under article 333 to represent the Anglo-Indian community shall be deemed to have been`
  line `nominated to represent the said community in the Legislative Assembly of Jharkhand under that article.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (26136)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Duration of Legislative Assemblies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26136&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The period of five years referred to in clause (1) of`
  line `article 172 shall, in the case of Legislative Assembly of the State of Bihar or Jharkhand be deemed to`
  line `have commenced on the date on which it actually commenced in the case of Legislative Assembly of the`
  line `existing State of Bihar.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (26137)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Speaker and Deputy Speaker.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26137&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The persons who immediately before the appointed day are`
  line `the Speaker and Deputy Speaker of the Legislative Assembly of the existing State of Bihar shall continue`
  line `to be the Speaker and Deputy Speaker respectively of that Assembly on and from that day.`
  line
  line `(2) As soon as may be after the appointed day, the Legislative Assembly of Jharkhand shall choose`
  line `two members of that Assembly to be respectively Speaker and Deputy Speaker thereof and until they are`
  line `so chosen, the duties of the office of Speaker shall be performed by such member of the Assembly as the`
  line `Governor may appoint for the purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (26138)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Rules of procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26138&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The rules of procedure and conduct of business of the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of Bihar as in force immediately before the appointed day shall, until rules are made under`
  line `clause (1) of article 208, be the rules of procedure and conduct of business of the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `Jharkhand, subject to such modifications and adaptations as may be made therein by the Speaker thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (26139)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Legislative Council of Bihar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26139&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `On and from the day on which all the members specified in the`
  line `Third Schedule retire, there shall be seventy-five seats in the Legislative Council of Bihar, and in the`
  line `Third Schedule to the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950), for the existing entry 2, the`
  line `following entry shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"2. Bihar 75 24 6 6 27 12".`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (26140)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Council constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26140&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, the Delimitation of Council`
  line `Constituencies (Bihar) Order, 1951 shall stand amended as directed in the Fourth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (26141)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Provision as to sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26141&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 17, all sitting`
  line `members of the Legislative Council of the existing State of Bihar, shall continue to be members of that`
  line `Council till they retire on the expiration of their present term of office.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (26142)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Chairman and Deputy Chairman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26142&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The person who immediately before the appointed day is`
  line `the Chairman or Deputy Chairman of the Legislative Council of the existing State of Bihar shall continue`
  line `to be the Chairman or Deputy Chairman, as the case may be, on and from that day of that Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (26143)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Delimitation of constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26143&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `section 12, the Election Commission shall determine in the manner hereinafter provided—`
  line
  line `(a) the number of seats to be reserved for the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes in the`
  line `Legislative Assemblies of the States of Bihar and Jharkhand respectively, having regard to the`
  line `relevant provisions of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(b) the assembly constituencies into which each State referred to in clause (a) shall be divided,`
  line `the extent of each of such constituencies and in which of them seats shall be reserved for the`
  line `Scheduled Castes or for the Scheduled Tribes; and`
  line
  line `(c) the adjustments in the boundaries and description of the extent of the parliamentary`
  line `constituencies in each successor States that may be necessary or expedient.`
  line
  line `(2) In determining the matters referred to in clauses (b) and (c) of sub-section (1), the Election`
  line `Commission shall have regard to the following provisions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) all the constituencies shall be single-member constituencies;`
  line
  line `(b) all constituencies shall, as far as practicable, be geographically compact areas, and in`
  line `delimiting them, regard shall be had to physical features, existing boundaries of administrative units,`
  line `facilities of communication and conveniences to the public; and`
  line
  line `(c) constituencies in which seats are reserved for the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes`
  line `shall, as far as practicable, be located in areas where the proportion of their population to the total`
  line `population is the largest.`
  line
  line `(3) The Election Commission shall, for the purpose of assisting it in the performance of its functions`
  line `under sub-section (1), associate with itself as associate members, five persons as the Central Government`
  line `may by order specify, being persons who are members of the Legislative Assembly of the State or of the`
  line `House of the People representing the State:`
  line
  line `Provided that none of the associate members shall have a right to vote or to sign any decision of the`
  line `Election Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) If, owing to death or resignation, the office of an associate member falls vacant, it shall be filled`
  line `as far as practicable, in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) The Election Commission shall—`
  line
  line `(a) publish its proposals for the delimitation of constituencies together with the dissenting`
  line `proposals, if any, of any associate member who desires publication thereof in the Official Gazette and`
  line `in such other manner as the Commission may consider fit, together with a notice inviting objections`
  line `and suggestions in relation to the proposals and specifying a date on or after which the proposals will`
  line `be further considered by it;`
  line
  line `(b) consider all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before the date so`
  line specified;
  line
  line `(c) after considering all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before the`
  line `date so specified, determine by one or more orders the delimitation of constituencies and cause such`
  line `order or orders to be published in the Official Gazette,`
  line
  line `and upon such publication, the order or orders shall have the full force of law and shall not be called in`
  line `question in any court.`
  line
  line `(6) As soon as may be after such publication, every such order relating to assembly constituencies`
  line `shall be laid before the Legislative Assembly of the concerned State.`
  line
  line `(7) The delimitation of constituencies in the States of Bihar and Jharkhand shall be determined on`
  line `the basis of the published figures of the census taken in the year 1971.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (26144)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power of the Election Commission to maintain Delimitation Orders up-to-date.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26144&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Election Commission may, from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette,—`
  line
  line `(a) correct any printing mistakes in any order made under section 21 or any error arising therein`
  line `from inadvertent slip or omission;`
  line
  line `(b) where the boundaries or name of any territorial division mentioned in any such order or orders`
  line `is or are altered, make such amendments as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for bringing such`
  line `order up-to-date.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification under this section relating to an assembly constituency shall be laid, as soon as`
  line `may be after it is issued, before the concerned Legislative Assembly.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (26145)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Amendment of the Scheduled Castes Order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26145&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, the Constitution`
  line `(Scheduled Castes) Order, 1950, shall stand amended as directed in the Fifth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (26146)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Amendment of the Scheduled Tribes Order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26146&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, the Constitution`
  line `(Scheduled Tribes) Order, 1950, shall stand amended as directed in the Sixth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (26147)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `High Court for Jharkhand.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26147&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, there shall be a separate High`
  line `Court for the State of Jharkhand (hereinafter referred to as the High Court of Jharkhand) and the High`
  line `Court at Patna shall become the High Court for the State of Bihar (hereinafter referred to as the High`
  line `Court at Patna).`
  line
  line `(2) The principal seat of the High Court of Jharkhand shall be at such place as the President may, by`
  line `notified order, appoint.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the Judges and division courts of the High`
  line `Court of Jharkhand may sit at such other place or places in the State of Jharkhand other than its principal`
  line `seat as the Chief Justice may, with the approval of the Governor of Jharkhand, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (26148)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Judges of High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26148&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Such of the Judges of the High Court at Patna holding office`
  line `immediately before the appointed day as may be determined by the President shall on that day cease to be`
  line `Judges of the High Court at Patna and become Judges of the High Court of Jharkhand.`
  line
  line `(2) The persons who by virtue of sub-section (1) become Judges of the High Court of Jharkhand shall,`
  line `except in the case where any such person is appointed to be the Chief Justice of that High Court, rank in`
  line `that Court according to the priority of their respective appointment as Judges of the High Court of Patna.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (26149)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Jurisdiction of High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26149&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The High Court of Jharkhand shall have, in respect of any part of`
  line `the territories included in the State of Jharkhand, all such jurisdiction, powers and authorities as, under the`
  line `law in force immediately before the appointed day, are exercisable in respect of that part of the said`
  line `territories by the High Court at Patna.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (26150)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Special provision relating to Bar Council and Advocates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26150&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day,`
  line `in the Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961), in section 3, in sub-section (1), in clause (a), after the words`
  line `"Jammu and Kashmir", the word "Jharkhand" shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who immediately before the appointed day is an advocate on the roll of the Bar`
  line `Council of the existing State of Bihar may give his option in writing, within one year from the appointed`
  line `day to the Bar Council of such existing State, to transfer his name on the roll of the Bar Council of`
  line `Jharkhand and notwithstanding anything contained in the Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961) and the rules`
  line `made thereunder, on such option so given his name shall be deemed to have been transferred on the roll`
  line `of the Bar Council of Jharkhand with effect from the date of the option so given for the purposes of the`
  line `said Act and the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(3) The person other than the advocates who are entitled immediately before the appointed day, to`
  line `practise in the High Court at Patna or any subordinate court thereof shall, on and after the appointed day,`
  line `be recognised as such persons entitled also to practise in the High Court of Jharkhand or any subordinate`
  line `court thereof, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) The right of audience in the High Court of Jharkhand shall be regulated in accordance with the`
  line `like principles as, immediately before the appointed day, are in force with respect to the right of audience`
  line `in the High Court at Patna.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (26151)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Practice and procedure in common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26151&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Part, the law`
  line `in force immediately before the appointed day with respect to practice and procedure in the High Court at`
  line `Patna shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in relation to the High Court of Jharkhand, and`
  line `accordingly, the High Court of Jharkhand shall have all such powers to make rules and orders with`
  line `respect to practice and procedure as immediately before the appointed day exercisable by the High Court`
  line `at Patna:`
  line
  line `Provided that any rules or orders which are in force immediately before the appointed day with`
  line `respect to practice and procedure in the High Court at Patna shall, until varied or revoked by rules or`
  line `orders made by the High Court of Jharkhand, apply with the necessary modifications in relation to`
  line `practice and procedure in the High Court of Jharkhand as if made by that court.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (26152)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Custody of seal of High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26152&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed day with`
  line `respect to the custody of the seal of the High Court at Patna shall with the necessary modifications, apply`
  line `with respect to the custody of the seal of the High court of Jharkhand.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (26153)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Form of writs and other processes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26153&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed day`
  line `with respect to the form of writs and special processes used, issued or awarded by the High Court at Patna`
  line `shall, with the necessary modificaitons, apply with respect to the form of writs and other processes used,`
  line `issued or awarded by the High Court of Jharkhand.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (26154)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Powers of Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26154&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed day relating to the`
  line `powers of the Chief Justice, single Judges and division courts of the High Court at Patna with respect to`
  line `all matters ancillary to the exercise of those powers shall, with the necessary modification, apply in`
  line `relation to the High Court of Jharkhand.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (26155)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Procedure as to appeals to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26155&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the`
  line `appointed day relating to appeals to the Supreme Court from the High Court at Patna and the Judges and`
  line `division courts thereof shall, with the necessary modification, apply in relation to the High Court of`
  line Jharkhand.
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (26156)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Transfer to proceedings from High Court at Patna to High Court of Jharkhand.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26156&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except`
  line `as hereinafter provided, the High Court at Patna shall, as from the appointed day, have no jurisdiction in`
  line `respect of the transferred territory.`
  line
  line `(2) Such proceedings pending in the High Court at Patna immediately before the appointed day as are`
  line `certified, whether before or after that day, by the Chief Justice of the High Court, having regard to the`
  line `places of accrual of the cause of action and both other circumstances, to be proceedings which are ought`
  line `to be heard and decided by the High Court of Jharkhand shall as soon as may be after such certification,`
  line `be transferred to the High Court of Jharkhand.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2) of this section or in section 27, but`
  line `save as hereinafter provided, the High Court at Patna shall have, and the High Court of Jharkhand shall`
  line `not have, jurisdiction to entertain, hear or dispose of appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the`
  line `Supreme Court, applications for review and other proceedings where any such proceedings seek any relief`
  line `in respect of any order passed by the High Court at Patna before the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that if after such proceedings have been entertained by the High Court at Patna, it appears to`
  line `the Chief Justice of the High Court that they ought to be transferred to the High Court of Jharkhand, he`
  line `shall order that they shall be so transferred, and such proceedings shall thereupon be transferred`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `(4) Any order made by the High Court at Patna—`
  line
  line `(a) before the appointed day, in any proceeding to the High Court of Jharkhand by virtue of`
  line `sub-section (2), or`
  line
  line `(b) in any proceedings with respect to which the High Court at Patna retains jurisdiction by virtue`
  line `of sub-section (3) shall for all purposes have effect, not only as an order or the High Court at Patna,`
  line `but also as an order made by the High Court of Jharkhand.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (26157)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Right to appear or to act in proceedings transferred to High Court of Jharkhand.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26157&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `person, who immediately before the appointed day, is an advocate entitled to practice or an attorney`
  line `entitled to act, in the High Court at Patna and so authorised to appear or to act in any proceedings`
  line `transferred from that High Court to the High Court of Jharkhand under section 34 shall have the right to`
  line `appear or to act, as the case may be, in the High Court of Jharkhand in relation to those proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (26158)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26158&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of section 34—`
  line
  line `(a) proceedings shall be deemed to be pending in a court until that court has disposed of all issues`
  line `between the parties, including any issues with respect to the taxation of the costs of the proceedings`
  line `and shall include appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the Supreme Court, application for`
  line `review, petitions for revision and petition for writs;`
  line
  line `(b) references to a High Court shall be construed as including references to a Judge or division`
  line `court thereof, and reference to order made by a court or the Judge shall be construed as including`
  line `references to a sentence, judgment or decree passed or made by that court of Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (26159)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title Saving.
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26159&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Part shall affect the application to the High Court of Jharkhand of any`
  line `provisions of the Constitution, and this Part shall have effect subject to any provision that may be made`
  line `on or after the appointed day with respect to that High Court by any Legislature or other authority having`
  line `power to make such provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (26160)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Authorisation of expenditure of Jharkhand State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26160&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `The Governor of Bihar may, at any time`
  line `before the appointed day, authorise such expenditure from the Consolidated Fund of the State of`
  line `Jharkhand as he deems necessary for any period not more than six months beginning with the appointed`
  line `day pending the sanction of such expenditure by the Legislative Assembly of the State of Jharkhand:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Governor of Jharkhand may, after the appointed day, authorise such further`
  line `expenditure as he deems necessary from the Consolidated Fund of the State of Jharkhand for any period`
  line `not extending beyond the said period of six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (26161)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Reports relating to accounts of Bihar State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26161&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The reports of the Comptroller and AuditorGeneral`
  line `of India referred to in clause (2) of article 151 relating to the accounts of the existing State of`
  line `Bihar in respect of any period prior to the appointed day shall be submitted to the Governor of each of the`
  line `successor States of Bihar and Jharkhand who shall cause them to be laid before the Legislature of that`
  line State.
  line
  line `(2) The President, after considering the views of the State Legislatures of the successor States, may`
  line `by order—`
  line
  line `(a) declare any expenditure incurred out of the Consolidated Fund of Bihar on any service in`
  line `respect of any period prior to the appointed day during the financial year or in respect of any earlier`
  line `financial year in excess of the amount granted for that service and for that year as disclosed in the`
  line `reports referred to in sub-section (1) to have been duly authorised; and`
  line
  line `(b) provide for any action to be taken on any matter arising out of the said reports.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (26162)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Distribution of revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26162&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `The President shall, by order, determine the share of States of Bihar`
  line `and Jharkhand in the total amount payable to the existing State of Bihar on the recommendation of the`
  line `Finance Commission constituted under article 280 of the Constitution, in such manner as he thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (26163)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Application of Part.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26163&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Part shall apply in relation to the apportionment`
  line `of the assets and liabilities of the existing State of Bihar immediately before the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) The successor States shall be entitled to receive benefits arising out of the decisions taken by the`
  line `predecessor State and the successor States shall be liable to bear the financial liabilities arising out of the`
  line `decisions taken by the existing State of Bihar.`
  line
  line `(3) The apportionment of assets and liabilities would be subject to such financial adjustment as may`
  line `be necessary to secure just, reasonable and equitable apportionment of the assets and liabilities amongst`
  line `the successor States.`
  line
  line `(4) Any dispute regarding the amount of financial assets and liabilities shall be settled through mutual`
  line `agreement, failing which by order, by the Central Government on the advice of the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (26164)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Land and goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26164&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to other provisions of this Part, all land and all stores, articles and`
  line `other goods belonging to the existing State of Bihar shall,`
  line
  line `(a) if within the transferred territory, pass to the State of Jharkhand; or`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, remain the property of the State of Bihar:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Central Government is of opinion that any goods or class of goods should be`
  line `distributed between the States of Bihar and Jharkhand, otherwise that according to the situation of the`
  line `goods, the Central Government may issue such directions as it thinks fit for a just and equitable`
  line `distribution of the goods and the goods shall pass to the successor States accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Stores held for specific purposes, such as use or utilisation in particular institutions, workshops or`
  line `undertakings or on particular works under construction, shall pass to the successor States in whose`
  line `territories such institutions, workshops, undertakings or works are located.`
  line
  line `(3) Stores relating to the Secretariat and offices of Heads of Departments having jurisdiction over the`
  line `whole of the existing State of Bihar shall be divided as may be agreed upon between the successor States,`
  line `or in default of such agreement, as the Central Government may by order direct for a just and equitable`
  line `distribution of such stores.`
  line
  line `(4) Any other unissued stores of any class in the existing State of Bihar shall be divided between the`
  line `successor States in proportion to the total stores of that class purchased in the period of three years prior`
  line `to the appointed day, for the territories of the existing State of Bihar included respectively in each of the`
  line `successor States:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such proportion cannot be ascertained in respect of any class of stores or where`
  line `the value of any class of such stores does not exceed rupees ten thousand, that class of stores shall be`
  line `divided between the successor States according to the population ratio.`
  line
  line `(5) In this section, the expression "land" includes immovable property of every kind and any rights in`
  line `or over such property, and the expression "goods" does not include coins, bank notes and currency notes.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (26165)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Treasury and bank balances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26165&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The total of the cash balances in all treasuries of the State of`
  line `Bihar and the credit balances of the State with Reserve Bank of India, the State Bank of India or any other`
  line `bank immediately before the appointed day shall be divided between the States of Bihar and Jharkhand`
  line `according to the population ratio:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the purposes of such division, there shall be no transfer of cash balances from any`
  line `treasury to any other treasury and the apportionment shall be effected by adjusting the credit balance of`
  line `the two States in the books of the Reserve Bank of India on the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the State of Jharkhand has no account on the appointed day with the Reserve`
  line `Bank of India, the adjustment shall be made in such manner as the Central Government may, by order,`
  line direct.
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (26166)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Arrears of taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26166&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `The right to recover arrears of any tax or duty on property, including arrears`
  line `of land revenue, shall belong to the successor State in which the property is situated, and the right to`
  line `recover arrears of any other tax or duty shall be long to the successor State in whose territories the place`
  line `of assessment of that tax or duty is included on the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (26167)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Right to recover loans and advances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26167&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) The right of the existing State of Bihar to recover`
  line `any loans or advances made before the appointed day to any local body, society, agriculturist or other`
  line `person in an area within that State shall belong to the successor State in which that area is included on`
  line `that day.`
  line
  line `(2) The right of the existing State of Bihar to recover any loans or advances made before the`
  line `appointed day to any person or institution outside that State shall belong to the State of Bihar:`
  line
  line `Provided that any sum recovered in respect of any such loan or advance shall be divided between the`
  line `States of Bihar and Jharkhand according to the population ratio.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (26168)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Investments and credits in certain funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26168&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The securities held in respect of the investments`
  line `made from Cash Balances Investment Account or from any Fund in the Public Account of the existing`
  line `State of Bihar as specified in the Seventh Schedule shall be apportioned in the ratio of population of the`
  line `successor States:`
  line
  line `Provided that the securities held in investments made from the Calamity Relief Fund of the existing`
  line `State of Bihar shall be divided in the ratio of the area of the territories occupied by the successor States:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the balance in the Reserve Funds in the Public Account of Bihar created wholly`
  line `out of appropriations from the Consolidated Fund of the existing State of Bihar, to the extent the balances`
  line `have not been invested outside Government account, shall not be carried forward to similar Reserve`
  line `Funds in the Public Account of, successor States.`
  line
  line `(2) The investments of the existing State of Bihar immediately before the appointed day, in any`
  line `special fund, the objects of which are confined to a local area, shall belong to the State in which that area`
  line `is included on the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(3) The investments of the existing State of Bihar immediately before the appointed day in any`
  line `private, commercial or industrial undertaking, in so far as such investments have not been made or are`
  line `deemed not to have been made from the cash balance investment account, shall pass to the State in which`
  line `the principal seat of business of the undertaking is located.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any body corporate constituted under a Central Act, State Act or Provincial Act for the`
  line `existing State of Bihar or any part thereof has, by virtue of the provisions of Part II, becomes an`
  line `inter-State body corporate, the investments in, or loans or advances to, any such body corporate by the`
  line `existing State of Bihar made before the appointed day shall, save as otherwise expressly provided by or`
  line `under this Act, be divided between the States of Bihar and Jharkhand in the same proportion in which the`
  line `assets of the body corporate are divided under the provisions of this Part.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (26169)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Assets and liabilities of State undertakings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26169&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The assets and liabilities relating to any`
  line `commercial or industrial undertaking of the existing State of Bihar shall pass to the State in which the`
  line `undertaking is located.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a depreciation reserve fund is maintained by the existing State of Bihar for any such`
  line `commercial or industrial undertaking, the securities held in respect of investments made from that fund`
  line `shall pass to the State in which the undertaking is located.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (26170)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Public Debt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26170&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) All liabilities on account of Public Debt and Public Account of the existing`
  line `State of Bihar outstanding immediately before the appointed day shall be apportioned in the ratio of`
  line `population of the successor States unless a different mode of apportionment is provided under the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The individual items of liabilities to be allocated to the successor States and the amount of`
  line `contribution required to be made by one successor State to another shall be such as may be ordered by the`
  line `Central Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India:`
  line
  line `Provided that till such orders are issued, the liabilities on account of Public Debt and Public Account`
  line `of the existing State of Bihar shall continue to be the liabilities of the successor State of Bihar.`
  line
  line `(3) The liability on account of loans raised from any source and re-lent by the existing State of Bihar`
  line `to such entities as may be specified by the Central Government and whose area of operation is confined to`
  line `either of the successor States shall devolve on the respective States as specified in sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(4) The public debt of the existing State of Bihar attributable to loan taken from any source for the`
  line `express purpose of re-lending the same to a specific institution and outstanding immediately before the`
  line `appointed day shall—`
  line
  line `(a) if re-lent to any local body, body corporate or other institution in any local area, be the debt of`
  line `the State in which the local area is included on the appointed day; or`
  line
  line `(b) if re-lent to the Bihar State Electricity Board, the Bihar State Road Transport Corporation, or`
  line `the Bihar Housing Board or any other institution which becomes an inter-State institution on the`
  line `appointed day, be divided between the States of Bihar and Jharkhand in the same proportion in which`
  line `the assets of such body corporate or institution are divided under the provisions of Part VII of this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(5) Where a sinking fund or a depreciation fund is maintained by the existing State of Bihar for`
  line `repayment of any loan raised by it, the securities held in respect of investments made from that fund shall`
  line `be divided between the successor States of Bihar and Jharkhand in the same proportion in which the total`
  line `public debt is divided between the two States under this section.`
  line
  line `(6) In this section, the expression "Government security" means a security created and issued by a`
  line `State Government for the purpose of raising a public loan and having any of the forms specified in, or`
  line `prescribed under clause (2) of section 2 of the Public Debt Act, 1944 (18 of 1944).`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (26171)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Floating Debt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26171&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The liability of the existing State of Bihar in respect of any floating loan to`
  line `provide short-term finance to any commercial undertaking shall be the liability of the State in whose`
  line `territories the undertaking is located.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (26172)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Refund of taxes collected in excess.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26172&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `The liability of the existing State of Bihar to refund any`
  line `tax or duty on property, including land revenue, collected in excess shall be the liability of the successor`
  line `State in whose territories the property is situated, and the liability of the existing State of Bihar to refund`
  line `any other tax or duty collected in excess shall be the liability of the successor State in whose territories`
  line `the place of assessment of that tax or duty is included.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (26173)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Deposits, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26173&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The liability of the existing State of Bihar in respect of any civil deposit or`
  line `loan fund deposit shall, as from the appointed day, be the liability of the State in whose area the deposit`
  line `has been made.`
  line
  line `(2) The liability of the existing State of Bihar in respect of any charitable or other endowment shall,`
  line `as from the appointed day, be the liability of the State in whose area the institution entitled to the benefit`
  line `of the endowment is located or of the State to which the objects of the endowment under the terms`
  line `thereof, are confined.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (26174)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Provident fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26174&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `The liability of the existing State of Bihar in respect of the provident fund`
  line `account of a Government servant in service on the appointed day shall, as from that day, be the liability of`
  line `the State to which that Government servant is permanently allotted.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (26175)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title Pensions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26175&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `The liability of the existing State of Bihar in respect of pensions and other retirement`
  line `benefits shall pass to, or be apportioned between, the successor States of Bihar and Jharkhand in`
  line `accordance with the provisions contained in the Eighth Schedule to this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (26176)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title Contracts.
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26176&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, before the appointed day, the existing State of Bihar has made any`
  line `contract in the exercise of its executive power for any purposes of the State, that contract shall be deemed`
  line `to have been made in the exercise of the executive power—`
  line
  line `(a) if the purposes of the contract are, on and from the appointed day, exclusive purposes of either`
  line `of the successor States of Bihar and Jharkhand; and`
  line
  line `(b) any other case, of the State of Bihar,`
  line
  line `and all rights and liabilities which have accrued, or may accrue under any such contract shall, to the`
  line `extent to which they would have been rights or liabilities of the existing State of Bihar, be rights or`
  line `liabilities of the State of Jharkhand or the State of Bihar, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that in any such case as is referred to in clause (b), the initial allocation of rights and`
  line `liabilities made by this sub-section shall be subject to such financial adjustment as may be agreed upon`
  line `between the successor States of Bihar and Jharkhand or in default of such agreement, as the Central`
  line `Government may, by order, direct.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, there shall be deemed to be included in the liabilities which have`
  line `accrued or may accrue under any contract—`
  line
  line `(a) any liability to satisfy an order or award made by any court or other tribunal in proceedings`
  line `relating to the contract; and`
  line
  line `(b) any liability in respect of expenses incurred in or in connection with any such proceedings.`
  line
  line `(3) This section shall have effect subject to the other provisions of this Part relating to the`
  line `apportionment of liabilities in respect of loans, guarantees and other financial obligations; and bank`
  line `balances and securities shall, notwithstanding that the partake of the nature of contractual rights, be dealt`
  line `with under those provisions.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (26177)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Liability in respect of actionable wrong.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26177&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the appointed day, the`
  line `existing State of Bihar is subject to any liability in respect of any actionable wrong other than breach of`
  line `contract, that liability shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if the cause of action arose wholly within the territories which, as from that day, are the`
  line `territories of either of the successor States of Bihar or Jharkhand, be a liability of that successor State;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, be initially a liability of the State of Bihar, but subject to such financial`
  line `adjustment as may be agreed upon between the States of Bihar and Jharkhand or, in default of such`
  line `agreement, as the Central Government may, by order, direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (26178)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Liability as guarantor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26178&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the appointed day, the existing State of`
  line `Bihar is liable as guarantor in respect of any liability of a registered co-operative society or other person,`
  line `that liability of the existing State of Bihar shall—`
  line
  line `(a) if the area of operations of such society or persons is limited to the territories which, as from`
  line `that day, are the territories of either of the States of Bihar or Jharkhand, be a liability of that successor`
  line `State; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, be initially a liability of the State of Bihar, subject to such financial`
  line `adjustment as may be agreed upon between the States of Bihar and Jharkhand or, in default of such`
  line `agreements, as the Central Government may, by order, direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (26179)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Items in suspense.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26179&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `If any item in suspense is ultimately found to affect an asset or liability of`
  line `the nature referred to in any of the foregoing provisions of this Part, it shall be dealt with in accordance`
  line `with that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (26180)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Residuary provision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26180&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `The benefit or burden of any asset or liability of the existing State of`
  line `Bihar not dealt with in the foregoing provisions of this Part shall pass to the State of Bihar in the first`
  line `instance, subject to such financial adjustment a may be agreed upon between the States of Bihar and`
  line `Jharkhand or, in default of such agreement, as the Central Government may, by order, direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (26181)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Apportionment of assets or liabilities by agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26181&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `Where the successor States of Bihar and`
  line `Jharkhand agree that the benefit or burden of any particular asset or liability should be apportioned`
  line `between them in a manner other than that provided for in the foregoing provisions of this Part,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained therein, the benefit or burden of that asset or liability shall be`
  line `apportioned in the manner agreed upon.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (26182)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Power of Central Government to order allocation or adjustment in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26182&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line Where,
  line `by virtue of any of the provisions of this Part, any of the successor States of Bihar and Jharkhand`
  line `becomes entitled to any property or obtains any benefits or becomes subject to any liability, and the`
  line `Central Government is of opinion, on a reference made within a period of three years from the appointed`
  line `day by either of the States, that it is just and equitable that property or those benefits should be transferred`
  line `to, or shared with, the other successor State, or that a contribution towards that liability should be made`
  line `by the other successor State, the said property or benefits shall be allocated in such manner between the`
  line `two States, or the other State shall make to the State subject to the liability such contribution in respect`
  line `thereof, as the Central Government may, after consultation with the two State Governments, by order,`
  line determine.
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (26183)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Certain expenditure to be charged on Consolidated Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26183&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `All sums payable either by the`
  line `State of Bihar or by the State of Jharkhand to the other States or by the Central Government to either of`
  line `those States, by virtue of the provisions of this Act, shall be charged on the Consolidated Fund of the`
  line `State by which such sums are payable or, as the case may be, the Consolidated Fund of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (26184)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Provisions as to Bihar State Electricity Board, State Warehousing Corporation and State Road Transport Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26184&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following bodies corporate constituted for the existing State of`
  line `Bihar, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the State Electricity Board constituted under the Electricity Supply Act, 1948 (54 of 1948);`
  line
  line `(b) the State Warehousing Corporation established under the Warehousing Corporations Act,`
  line `1962 (58 of 1962);`
  line
  line `(c) the State Road Transport Corporation established under the Road Transport Act, 1950`
  line `(64 of 1950),`
  line
  line `shall, on and from the appointed day, continue to function in those areas in respect of which they were`
  line `functioning immediately before that day, subject to the provisions of this section and to such directions as`
  line `may, from time to time, be issued by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Any directions issued by the Central Government under sub-section (1) in respect of the Board or`
  line `the Corporation shall include a direction that the Act under which the Board or the Corporation was`
  line `constituted shall, in its application to that Board or Corporation, have effect subject to such exceptions`
  line `and modifications as the Central Government thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board or the Corporation referred to in sub-section (1) shall cease to function as from, and`
  line `shall be deemed to be dissolved on such date as the Central Government may, by order, appoint; and upon`
  line `such dissolution, its assets, rights and liabilities shall be apportioned between the successor States of`
  line `Bihar and Jharkhand in such manner as may be agreed upon between them within one year of the`
  line `dissolution of the Board or the Corporation, as the case may be, or if no agreement is reached, in such`
  line `manner as the Central Government may, by order, determine:`
  line
  line `Provided that any liabilities of the said Board relating to the unpaid dues of the coal supplied to the`
  line `Board by any public sector coal company shall be provisionally apportioned between the State Electricity`
  line `Boards constituted respectively in the successor States of the existing State of Bihar or after the date`
  line `appointed for the dissolution of the Board under this sub-section in such manner as may be agreed upon`
  line `between the Governments of the successor States within one month of such dissolution or if no agreement`
  line `is reached, in such manner as the Central Government may, by order, determine subject to reconciliation`
  line `and finalisation of the liabilities which shall be completed within three months from the date of such`
  line `dissolution by the mutual agreement between the successor States or failing such agreement by the`
  line `direction of the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided further that an interest at the rate of two per cent. higher than the Cash Credit interest shall`
  line `be paid on outstanding unpaid dues of the coal supplied to the Board by the public sector coal company`
  line `till the liquidation of such dues by the concerned State Electricity Board constituted in the successor`
  line `States on or after the date appointed for the dissolution of the Board under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in the preceding provisions of this section shall be construed as preventing the`
  line `Government of the State of Bihar, or, as the case may be, the Government of the State of Jharkhand from`
  line `constituting, at any time on or after the appointed day, State Electricity Board or a State Warehousing`
  line `Corporation or a Road Transport Corporation for the State under the provisions of the Act relating to such`
  line `Board or Corporation; and if such a Board or Corporation is so constituted in either of the States before`
  line `the dissolution of the Board or the Corporation referred to in sub-section (1),—`
  line
  line `(a) provision may be made by order of the Central Government enabling the new Board or the`
  line `new Corporation to take over from the existing Board or Corporation all or any of its undertakings,`
  line `assets, rights and liabilities in that State, and`
  line
  line `(b) upon the dissolution of the existing Board or Corporation,—`
  line
  line `(i) any assets, rights and liabilities which would otherwise have passed to that State by or`
  line `under the provisions of sub-section (3) shall pass to the new Board or the new Corporation`
  line `instead of to that State;`
  line
  line `(ii) any employee who would otherwise have been transferred to or re-employed by that State`
  line `under sub-section (3), read with clause (i) of sub-section (5), shall be transferred to or`
  line `re-employed by the new Board or the new Corporation instead of to or by that State.`
  line
  line `(5) An agreement entered into between the successor States under sub-section (3) and an order made`
  line `by the Central Government under that sub-section or under clause (a) of sub-section (4) may provide for`
  line `the transfer or re-employment of any employee of the Board or the Corporation referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1),—`
  line
  line `(i) to or by the successor States, in the case of an agreement under sub-section (4) or an order`
  line `made under that sub-section;`
  line
  line `(ii) to or by the new Board or the new Corporation constituted under sub-section (4), in the`
  line `case of an order made under clause (a) of that sub-section,`
  line
  line `and, subject to the provisions of section 65, also for the terms and conditions of service applicable to such`
  line `employees after such transfer or re-employment.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (26185)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Continuance of arrangements in regard to generation and supply of electric power and supply of water.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26185&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `If it appears to the Central Government that the arrangement in regard to the`
  line `generation or supply of electric power or the supply of water for any area or in regard to the execution of`
  line `any project for such generation or supply has been or is likely to be modified to the disadvantage of that`
  line `area by reason of the fact that it is, by virtue of the provisions of Part II of this Act, outside the State in`
  line `which the power stations and other installations for the generation and supply of such power, or the`
  line `catchment area, reservoirs and other works for the supply of water, as the case may be, are located, the`
  line `Central Government may give such directions as it deems proper to the State Government or other`
  line `authority concerned for the maintenance, so far as practicable, of the previous arrangement.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (26186)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Provisions as to Bihar State Financial Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26186&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bihar State Financial`
  line `Corporation established under the State Financial Corporation Act, 1951 (63 of 1951) shall, on and from`
  line `the appointed day, continue to function in those areas in respect of which it was functioning immediately`
  line `before that day, subject to the provisions of this section and to such directions as may, from time to time,`
  line `be issued by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Any directions issued by the Central Government under sub-section (1) in respect of the`
  line `Corporation may include a direction that the said Act, in its application to the Corporation, shall have`
  line `effect subject to such exceptions and modifications as may be specified in the direction.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the Board of Directors`
  line `of the Corporation may, with the previous approval of the Central Government and shall, if so required by`
  line `the Central Government, convene at any time after the appointed day a meeting for the consideration of a`
  line `scheme for the reconstitution or reorganisation or dissolution, as the case may be, of the Corporation,`
  line `including proposals regarding the formation of new Corporation, and the transfer thereto of the assets,`
  line `rights and liabilities of the existing Corporation, and if such a scheme is approved at the general meeting`
  line `by a resolution passed by a majority of the shareholders present and voting, the scheme shall be submitted`
  line `to the Central Government for its sanction.`
  line
  line `(4) If the scheme is sanctioned by the Central Government either without modifications or with`
  line `modifications which are approved at a general meeting, the Central Government shall certify the scheme,`
  line `and upon such certification, the scheme shall, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any`
  line `law for the time being in force, be binding on the corporations affected by the scheme as well as the`
  line `shareholders and creditors thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) If the scheme is not so approved or sanctioned, the Central Government may refer the scheme to`
  line `such Judge of the High Court at Patna and Jharkhand as may be nominated in this behalf by the Chief`
  line `Justice thereof, and the decision of the Judge in regard to the scheme shall be final and shall be binding on`
  line `the corporations affected by the scheme as well as the shareholders and creditors thereof.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing in the preceding provisions of this section shall be construed as preventing the`
  line `Government of the States of Bihar and Jharkhand from constituting, at any time on or after the appointed`
  line `day, a State Financial Corporation for that State under the State Financial Corporations`
  line `Act, 1951 (63 of 1951).`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (26187)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Provisions as to certain companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26187&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Part, each of the companies specified in the Ninth Schedule to this Act shall, on and`
  line `from the appointed day and until otherwise provided for in any law, or in any agreement among the`
  line `successor States, or in any direction issued by the Central Government, continue to function in the areas`
  line `in which it was functioning immediately before that day; and the Central Government may, from time to`
  line `time, issue such directions in relation to such functioning as it may deem fit, notwithstanding anything to`
  line `the contrary contained in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or in any other law.`
  line
  line `(2) Any directions issued under sub-section (1) in respect of a company referred to in that`
  line `sub-section, may include directions—`
  line
  line `(a) regarding the division of the interests and shares of existing state of Bihar in the company`
  line `among the successor States;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the reconstitution of the Board of Directors of the company so as to give adequate`
  line `representation to both the successor States.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (26188)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `General provision as to statutory corporations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26188&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise expressly provided by`
  line `the foregoing provisions of this Part, where anybody corporate constituted under a Central Act, State Act`
  line `or Provincial Act for the existing State of Bihar or any part thereof has, by virtue of the provisions of`
  line `Part II of this Act, become an inter-State body corporate, then, the body corporate shall, on and from the`
  line `appointed day, continue to function and operate in those areas in respect of which it was functioning and`
  line `operating immediately before that day, subject to such directions as may from time to time be issued by`
  line `the Central Government, until other provision is made by law in respect of the said body corporate.`
  line
  line `(2) Any directions issued by the Central Government under sub-section (1) in respect of any such`
  line `body corporate shall include a direction that any law by which the said body corporate is governed shall,`
  line `in its application to that body corporate, have effect subject to such exceptions and modifications as may`
  line `be specified in the direction.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (26189)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Temporary provisions as to continuance of certain existing road transport permits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26189&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 88 of the Motor Vehicles Act, 1988 (59 of 1988) a permit`
  line `granted by the State Transport Authority of the existing State of Bihar or any Regional Transport`
  line `Authority in that State shall, if such permit was, immediately before the appointed day, valid and effective`
  line `in any area in the transferred territory, be deemed to continue to be valid and effective in that area after`
  line `that day subject to the provisions of that Act as for the time being in force in that area; and it shall not be`
  line `necessary for any such permit to be countersigned by the State Transport Authority of Jharkhand or any`
  line `Regional Transport Authority therein for the purpose of validating it for use in such area:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, after consultation with the successor State Government or`
  line `Governments concerned add to, amend or vary the conditions attached to the permit by the Authority by`
  line `which the permit was granted.`
  line
  line `(2) No tolls, entrance fees or other charges of a like nature shall be levied after the appointed day in`
  line `respect of any transport vehicle for its operations in any of the successor States under any such permit, if`
  line `such vehicle was, immediately before that day, exempt from the payment of any such toll, entrance fees`
  line `or other charges for its operations in the transferred territory:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, after consultation with the State Government or`
  line `Governments concerned, authorise the levy of any such toll, entrance fees or other charges, as the case`
  line `may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (26190)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Special provisions relating to retrenchment compensation in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26190&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `Where on`
  line `account of the reorganisation of the existing State of Bihar under this Act, any body corporate constituted`
  line `under a Central Act, State Act or Provincial Act, any co-operative society registered under any law`
  line `relating to co-operative societies or any commercial or industrial undertaking of that State is reconstituted`
  line `or reorganised in any manner whatsoever or is amalgamated with any other body corporate, co-operative society or undertaking, or is dissolved, and in consequence of such reconstitution, reorganisation,`
  line `amalgamation or dissolution, any workman employed by such body corporate or in any such co-operative`
  line `society or undertaking, is transferred to, or re-employed by any other body corporate, or in any other`
  line `co-operative society or undertaking, then notwithstanding anything contained in section 25F, 25FF or`
  line `25FFF of the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947) such transfer or re-employment shall not entitle`
  line `in to any compensation under that section:`
  line
  line `Provided that—`
  line
  line `(a) the terms and conditions of service applicable to the workman after such transfer or`
  line `re-employment are not less favorable to the workman than those applicable to him immediately`
  line `before the transfer or re-employment;`
  line
  line `(b) the employer in relation to the body corporate, the co-operative society or the undertaking`
  line `where the workman transferred or re-employed is, by agreement or otherwise, legally liable to pay to`
  line `the workman, in the event of his retrenchment, compensation under section 25F, 25FF or 25FFF of`
  line `the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947) on the basis that his service has been continuous and`
  line `has not been interrupted by the transfer or re-employment.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (26191)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Special provision as to income-tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26191&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `Where the assets, rights and liabilities of any body`
  line `corporate carrying on business are, under the provisions of this Part, transferred to any other bodies`
  line `corporate which after the transfer carry on the same business, the losses or profits or gains sustained by`
  line `the body corporate first mentioned which, but for such transfer, would have been allowed to be carried`
  line `forward and set off in accordance with the provisions of Chapter VI of the Income-tax Act,`
  line `1961 (43 of 1961) shall be apportioned amongst the transferee bodies corporate in accordance with the`
  line `rules to be made by the Central Government in this behalf and, upon such apportionment, the share of`
  line `loss allotted to each transferee body corporate shall be dealt with in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `Chapter VI of the said Act, as if the transferee body corporate had itself sustained such loss in a business`
  line `carried on by it in the years in which these losses were sustained.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (26192)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Continuance of facilities in certain State institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26192&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government of State of Bihar`
  line `or Jharkhand, as the case may be, shall, in respect of the institutions specified in the Tenth Schedule to`
  line `this Act, located in that State, continue to provide facilities to the people of the other State which shall`
  line `not, in any respect, be less favourable to such people than what were being provided to them before the`
  line `appointed day, for such period and upon such terms and conditions as may be agreed upon between the`
  line `two State Governments before the 1st day of December, 2001 or if no agreement is reached by the said`
  line `date as may be fixed by order of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, at any time before the 1st day of December, 2001 by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, specify in the Tenth Schedule any other institution existing on the appointed day in`
  line `the States of Bihar and Jharkhand and on the issue of such notification, the Schedule shall be deemed to`
  line `be amended by the inclusion of the said institution therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (26193)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Provisions relating to All-India Services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26193&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this section, the expression "State cadre"—`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to the Indian Administrative Service, has the meaning assigned to it in the Indian`
  line `Administrative Service (Cadre) Rules, 1954;`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to the Indian Police Service, has the meaning assigned to it in the Indian Police`
  line `Service (Cadre) Rules, 1954; and`
  line
  line `(c) in relation to the Indian Forest Service, has the meaning assigned to it in the Indian Forest`
  line `Service (Cadre) Rules, 1966.`
  line
  line `(2) In place of the cadres of the Indian Administrative Service, Indian Police Service and Indian`
  line `Forest Service for the existing State of Bihar, there shall, on and from the appointed day, be two separate`
  line `cadres, one for the State of Bihar and the other for the State of Jharkhand in respect of each of these`
  line services.
  line
  line `(3) The initial strength and composition of the State cadres referred to in sub-section (2) shall be such`
  line `as the Central Government may, by order, determine before the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(4) The members of each of the said service borne on the Bihar cadre thereof immediately before the`
  line `appointed day shall be allocated to the State cadres of the same service constituted under sub-section (2)`
  line `in such manner and with effect from such date or dates as the Central Government may, by order, specify`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect the operation, on or after the appointed day, of`
  line `the All-India Service Act, 1951 (61 of 1951) or the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (26194)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Provisions relating to services in Bihar and Jharkhand.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26194&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who immediately`
  line `before the appointed day is serving in connection with the affairs of the existing State of Bihar shall, on`
  line `and from that day provisionally continue to serve in connection with the affairs of the State of Bihar`
  line `unless he is required, by general or special order of the Central Government to serve provisionally in`
  line `connection with the affairs of the State of Jharkhand:`
  line
  line `Provided that no direction shall be issued under this section after the expiry of a period of one year`
  line `from the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) As soon as may be after the appointed day, the Central Government shall, by general or special`
  line `order, determine the successor State to which every person referred to in sub-section (1) shall be finally`
  line `allotted for service and the date with effect from which such allotment shall take effect or be deemed to`
  line `have taken effect.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person who is finally allotted under the provisions of sub-section (2) to a successor State`
  line `shall, if he is not already serving therein be made available for serving in the successor State from such`
  line `date as may be agreed upon between the Governments concerned or in default of such agreement, as may`
  line `be determined by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (26195)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Other provisions relating to services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26195&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in section 72 shall be deemed to affect on or`
  line `after the appointed day the operation of the provisions of Chapter I of Part XIV of the Constitution in`
  line `relation to determination of the conditions of service of persons serving in connection with the affairs of`
  line `the Union or any State:`
  line
  line `Provided that the conditions of service applicable immediately before the appointed day in the case of`
  line `any person deemed to have been allocated to the State of Bihar or to the State of Jharkhand under`
  line `section 72 shall not be varied to his disadvantage except with the previous approval of the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) All services prior to the appointed day rendered by a person—`
  line
  line `(a) if he is deemed to have been allocated to any State under section 72, shall be deemed to have`
  line `been rendered in connection with the affairs of that State;`
  line
  line `(b) if he is deemed to have been allocated to the Union in connection with the administration of`
  line `the Jharkhand shall be deemed to have been rendered in connection with the affairs of the Union,`
  line
  line `for the purposes of the rules regulating his conditions of service.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of section 72, shall not apply in relation to members of any All-India Service.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (26196)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Provisions as to continuance of officers in same post.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26196&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `Every person who, immediately before`
  line `the appointed day is holding or discharging the duties of any post or office in connection with the affairs`
  line `of the existing State of Bihar in any area which on that day falls within any of the successor States shall`
  line `continue to hold the same post or office in that successor State, and shall be deemed, on and from that`
  line `day, to have been duly appointed to the post or office by the Government of, or any other appropriate`
  line `authority in, that successor State:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent a competent authority, on and from`
  line `the appointed day, from passing in relation to such person any order affecting the continuance in such`
  line `post or office.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (26197)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Advisory Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26197&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may by order establish one or more Advisory`
  line `Committees for the purpose of assisting it in regard to—`
  line
  line `(a) the discharge of any of its functions under this Part; and`
  line
  line `(b) the ensuring of fair and equitable treatment to all persons affected by the provisions of this`
  line `Part and the proper consideration of any representations made by such persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (26198)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26198&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give such`
  line `directions to the State Government of Bihar and the State Government of Jharkhand as may appear to it to`
  line `be necessary for the purpose of giving effect to the foregoing provisions of this Part and the State`
  line `Government shall comply with such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (26199)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Provisions as to State Public Service Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26199&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Public Service Commission for`
  line `the existing State of Bihar shall, on and from the appointed day, be the Public Service Commission for the`
  line `State of Bihar.`
  line
  line `(2) The persons holding office immediately before the appointed day as Chairman or other member of`
  line `the Public Service Commission for the existing State of Bihar shall, as from the appointed day, be the`
  line `Chairman or, as the case may be, the other member of the Public Service Commission for the State of`
  line Bihar.
  line
  line `(3) Every person who becomes Chairman or other member of the Public Service Commission for the`
  line `State of Bihar on the appointed day under sub-section (2), shall—`
  line
  line `(a) be entitled to receive from the Government of the State of Bihar conditions of service not less`
  line `favourable than those to which he was entitled under the provisions applicable to him;`
  line
  line `(b) subject to the proviso to clause (2) of article 316, hold office or continue to hold office until`
  line `the expiration of his term of office as determined under the provisions applicable to him immediately`
  line `before the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(4) The report of the Bihar Public Service Commission as to the work done by the Commission in`
  line `respect of any period prior to the appointed day shall be presented under clause (2) of article 323 to the`
  line `Governors of the States of Bihar and Jharkhand, and the Governor of the State of Bihar shall, on receipt`
  line `of such report, cause a copy thereof together with a memorandum explaining as far as possible, as`
  line `respects the cases, if any, where the advice of the Commission was not accepted, the reasons for such`
  line `non-acceptance to be laid before the Legislature of the State of Bihar and it shall not be necessary to`
  line `cause such report or any such memorandum to be laid before the Legislative Assembly of the State of`
  line Jharkhand.
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (26200)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Water Resources Development and its Management.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26200&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in this Act but subject to the provisions of section 79, all rights and liabilities of the existing State of`
  line `Bihar in relation to water resource projects in relation to,—`
  line
  line `(i) Ganga and its tributaries; and`
  line
  line `(ii) Sone and its tributaries,`
  line
  line `shall, on the appointed day be the rights and liabilities of the successor States in such proportion as may`
  line `be fixed and subject to such adjustments as may be made, by agreement entered into by the said States`
  line `after consultation with the Central Government, or, if no such agreement is entered into within two years`
  line `of the appointed day, then the Central Government may, by order, determine within one year having`
  line `regard to the purposes of the project:`
  line
  line `Provided that the order so made by the Central Government may be varied by any subsequent`
  line `agreement entered into by the successor States after consultation with the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) An agreement or order referred to in sub-section (1) shall, where an extension or further`
  line `development of any of the projects referred to in that sub-section after the appointed day is undertaken, be`
  line `the rights and liabilities of the successor States in relation to such extension or further development.`
  line
  line `(3) The rights and liabilities referred to in sub-sections (1) and (2) shall include,—`
  line
  line `(a) the right to receive and utilise the water available for distribution as a result of the projects;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) the right to receive and utilise the power generated as a result of the projects,`
  line
  line `but shall not include the rights and liabilities under any contract entered into before the appointed day by`
  line `the Government of the existing State of Bihar with any person or authority other than Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (26201)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Constitution and functions of Management Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26201&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall`
  line `constitute a Board to be called the Ganga and Sone Management Board (hereinafter referred to as the`
  line `Board) for administration, construction, maintenance and operation of projects referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 78 for any or for a combination of following purposes, namely:`
  line
  line `(i) Irrigation;`
  line
  line `(ii) Rural and Urban Water Supply;`
  line
  line `(iii) Hydro Power generation;`
  line
  line `(iv) Navigation;`
  line
  line `(v) Industries; and`
  line
  line `(vi) for any other purpose which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall consist of`
  line
  line `(a) a whole-time Chairman and two whole-time members to be appointed by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(b) a representative each of the Government of the States of Uttar Pradesh, Bihar, Jharkhand`
  line `and Madhya Pradesh to be nominated by the respective Governments;`
  line
  line `(c) two representatives of the Central Government to be nominated by that Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The functions of the Board shall include`
  line
  line `(a) the regulation of supply of water from the projects referred to in sub-section (1) of section 78`
  line `to States of Uttar Pradesh, Bihar, Jharkhand and Madhya Pradesh having regard to--`
  line
  line `(i) any agreement entered into or arrangement made covering the Governments of existing`
  line `State of Bihar and the States of Uttar Pradesh, Bihar, Jharkhand and Madhya Pradesh, and`
  line
  line `(ii) the agreement or the order referred to in sub-section (2) of section 78;`
  line
  line `(b) the regulation of supply of power generated at the projects referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 78, to any Electricity Board or other authority incharge of the distribution of power having`
  line `regard to`
  line
  line `(i) any agreement entered into or arrangement made covering the Governments of existing`
  line `State of Bihar and the States of Uttar Pradesh, Bihar, Jharkhand and Madhya Pradesh, and`
  line
  line `(ii) the agreement or the order referred to in sub-section (2) of section 78;`
  line
  line `(c) the examination of the requirement of funds for various projects in terms of the programme`
  line `laid down for such projects and to advise the apportionment of the expenditure to the participating`
  line `States keeping in view the agreement on the sharing of cost;`
  line
  line `(d) to decide the withdrawal of water from the reservoirs during the construction period for`
  line `irrigation and power purposes with a view to securing better use of available water;`
  line
  line `(e) the responsibility of devising programme of resettlement for persons displaced as a result of`
  line `Irrigation Projects;`
  line
  line `(f) construction of such of the remaining or new works connected with the development of the`
  line `water resource project relating to the rivers or their tributaries as the Central Government may specify`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette; and`
  line
  line `(g) such other functions as the Central Government may after consultation with the Governments`
  line `of the States of Uttar Pradesh, Bihar, Jharkhand and Madhya Pradesh entrust to it.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (26202)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Staff of the Management Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26202&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may employ such staff, as it may consider`
  line `necessary for the efficient discharge of its functions under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that every person who immediately before the constitution of the said Board was`
  line `engaged in the construction, maintenance or operation of the works relating to the projects referred to`
  line `in sub-section (1) of section 78 shall continue to be so employed under the Board in connection with`
  line `the said works on the same terms and conditions of the service as were applicable to him before such`
  line `constitution until the Central Government by order, directs otherwise:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the said Board may at any time in consultation with the State Governments`
  line `or the Electricity Board concerned and with prior approval of the Central Government retain any such`
  line `person for service under that State Government or Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Government of the States of Uttar Pradesh, Bihar, Jharkhand and Madhya Pradesh shall`
  line `at all times provide the necessary funds to the Board to meet all expenses (including the salaries and`
  line `allowances of the staff) required for the discharge of its functions and such amounts shall be`
  line `apportioned among the States concerned in such proportion as the Central Government may having`
  line `regard to the benefits to each of the said States specify.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall be under the control of the Central Government and shall comply with such`
  line `directions, as may from time to time, be given to it by that Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board may, with the approval of the Central Government delegate such of its powers,`
  line `functions and duties as it may deem fit to the Chairman of the said Board or to any officer`
  line `subordinate to the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may, for the purpose of enabling the Board to function efficiently,`
  line `issue such directions to the State Governments concerned, or any other authority, and the State`
  line `Governments, or the other authority shall comply with such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (26203)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Jurisdiction of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26203&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall, ordinarily exercise jurisdiction in regard to`
  line `any of the projects referred to in sub-section (1) of section 78 over headwork (barrages, dams,`
  line `reservoir, regulating construction), part of canal network and transmission lines necessary to deliver`
  line `water or power to the States concerned.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether the Board has jurisdiction under sub-section (1) over any`
  line `project referred thereto, the same shall be referred to the Central Government for decision thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (26204)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26204&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, with the prior approval of the Central`
  line `Government by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations consistent with this Act and`
  line `orders made thereunder, to provide for—`
  line
  line `(a) regulating the time and place of meetings of the Board and the procedure to be followed`
  line `for the transaction of business at such meetings;`
  line
  line `(b) delegation of powers and duties to the Chairman or any officer of the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) the appointment and regulation of the conditions of service of the officers and other staff`
  line `of the Board; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter for which regulations are considered necessary by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (26205)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Amendment of Act 37 of 1956.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26205&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in section 15 of the States`
  line `Reorganisation Act, 1956, in clause (c), for the word "Bihar", the words`
  line `"Bihar and Jharkhand" shall be`
  line substituted.
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (26206)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Territorial extent of laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26206&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of Part II of this Act shall not be deemed to have`
  line `effected any change in the territories to which any law in force immediately before the appointed day`
  line `extends or applies, and territorial references in any such law to the State of Bihar shall, until otherwise`
  line `provided by a competent Legislature or other competent authority be construed as meaning the territories`
  line `within the existing State of Bihar before the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (26207)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Power to adapt laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26207&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of facilitating the application in relation to the State of`
  line `Bihar or Jharkhand of any law made before the appointed day, the appropriate Government may, before`
  line `the expiration of two years from that day, by order, make such adaptations and modifications of the law,`
  line `whether by way of repeal or amendment, as may be necessary or expedient, and thereupon every such law`
  line `shall have effect subject to the adaptations and modifications so made until altered, repealed or amended`
  line `by a competent Legislature or other competent authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, the expression "appropriate Government" means as respects any law`
  line `relating to a matter enumerated in the Union List, the Central Government, and as respects any other law`
  line `in its application to a State, the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (26208)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Power to construe laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26208&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding that no provision or insufficient provision has been`
  line `made under section 85 for the adaptation of a law made before the appointed day, any court, tribunal or`
  line `authority, required or empowered to enforce such law may, for the purpose of facilitating its application`
  line `in relation to the State of Bihar or Jharkhand, construe the law in such manner, without affecting the`
  line `substance, as may be necessary or proper in regard to the matter before the court, tribunal or authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (26209)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Power to name authorities, etc., for exercising statutory functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26209&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `The Government of the`
  line `State of Jharkhand, as respects the transferred territory may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify the authority, officer or person who, on or after the appointed day, shall be competent to exercise`
  line `such functions exercisable under any law in force on that day as may be mentioned in that notification`
  line `and such law shall have effect accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (26210)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26210&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `Where immediately before the appointed day, the existing State of Bihar is`
  line `a party to any legal proceedings with respect to any property, rights or liabilities subject to apportionment`
  line `between the States of Bihar and Jharkhand under this Act, the State of Bihar or Jharkhand which succeeds`
  line `to, or acquires a share in, that property or those rights or liabilities by virtue of any provision of this Act`
  line `shall be deemed to be substituted for the existing State of Bihar or added as a part to those proceedings,`
  line `and the proceedings may continue accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (26211)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Transfer of pending proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26211&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every proceeding pending immediately before the`
  line `appointed day before a court (other than the High Court), tribunal, authority or officer in any area which`
  line `on that day falls within the State of Bihar shall, if it is a proceeding relating exclusively to the territory,`
  line `which as from that day is the territory of Jharkhand State, stand transferred to the corresponding court,`
  line `tribunal, authority or officer of that State.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether any proceeding should stand transferred under sub-section (1),`
  line `it shall be referred to the High Court at Patna and the decision of that High Court shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section—`
  line
  line `(a) "proceeding" includes any suit, case or appeal; and`
  line
  line `(b) "corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer" in the State of Jharkhand means—`
  line
  line `(i) the court, tribunal, authority or officer in which, or before whom, the proceeding would`
  line `have laid if it had been instituted after the appointed day; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of doubt, such court, tribunal, authority, or officer in that State, as may be`
  line `determined after the appointed day by the Government of that State or the Central Government,`
  line `as the case may be, or before the appointed day by the Government of the existing State of Bihar`
  line `to be the corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (26212)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Right of pleaders to practise in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26212&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `Any person who, immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, is enrolled as a pleader entitled to practise in any subordinate courts in the existing State of`
  line `Bihar shall, for a period of one year from that day continue to be entitled to practise in those courts,`
  line `notwithstanding that the whole or any part of the territories within the jurisdiction of those courts has`
  line `been transferred to the State of Jharkhand.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (26213)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Effect of provisions of the Act inconsistent with other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26213&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall`
  line `have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (26214)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285&sectionId=26214&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00043_200030_1517807324285
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the President may, by order, do anything not inconsistent with such provisions which appears to`
  line `him to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of three years from the`
  line `appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
